				\begin{document}$$\begin{array}{*{20}{l}} {{\mathrm{ln}}\left( {{\mathrm{TiO}}_2} \right)_{{\mathrm{melt}}}} \hfill & = \hfill & {{\mathrm{ln}}\left( {{\mathrm{TiO}}_2} \right)_{{\mathrm{rutile}}} \, + \, 1.701 - \left( {\frac{{9041}}{T}} \right)} \hfill \\ {} \hfill & {} \hfill & { - \, 0.173P + 0.348{\mathrm{FM}} + 0.016{\mathrm{H}}_2{\mathrm{O}}} \hfill \end{array},$$\end{document}lnTiO2melt=lnTiO2rutile+1.701-9041T-0.173P+0.348FM+0.016H2O,where TiO2 and H2O are in wt.%, T and P are in K and GPa, respectively. We assumed the water content in differentiated arc magmas is 6 wt.%. FM is a melt composition term calculated as:3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
